  <section class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <Image
      src={scooter}
      alt="scooter"
      class="absolute -bottom-48 right-4 z-[-8] w-max py-8"
    />
    <h1 class="text-unicyclePrimary text-8xl">
      User
      <p class="text-slate-800">Research</p>
    </h1>

    <article>
      <h2 class="">Research Methodology</h2>
      <p class="">
        As a method of qualitative research was chosen, one-on-one interviews
        with the targeted audience were conducted.
      </p>
      <p
        class="font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-[#6d45df] to-[#e6575a] bg-clip-text text-transparent"
      >
        Why?
      </p>
      <p class="">
        A qualitative type of research was chosen because quantitative research
        in this step of the process won’t give necessary answers and won’t
        provide answers to the following questions:
      </p>
      <li class="">
        What problems do users face when they want to use a micro-mobility
        service?
      </li>
      <li class="">What product should I create?</li>
      <li class="">
        What is important to users when they use micro-mobility services?
      </li>
      <li class="">And how to solve these problems?</li>
      <p>
        Interviews, in this case, are much more effective than surveys, as they
        provide an opportunity to collect in-depth information about people’s
        opinions, thoughts, experiences, and feelings.
      </p>
      <h2 class="">Research Goals</h2>
      <p>
        Imbued with the user experience and understand their pain points and
        needs.
      </p>
      <h2 class="">Research Question</h2>
      <p>
        To learn about users' interests, goals, and desires related to
        micro-mobility services.
      </p>
      <h2 class="">Research Objectives</h2>
      <li class="">
        Uncover participants' attitudes towards and thought processes around
        utilizing micro-mobility services
      </li>
      <li class="">
        Understand the process, and tools participants use for accessing
        information about what micro-mobility services are in their
        area/available.
      </li>
      <h2 class="">Interview Format</h2>
      <p>Interviews were conducted via Zoom and in person.</p>
      <h2 class="">Information about Respondents</h2>
      <p>The respondents’ names were changed to ensure confidentiality.</p>
      <p>
        We identified a group of potential representatives of the target
        audience who need to be involved in the interview:
      </p>
      <li class="">
        People who are already using the micro-mobility services, but have some
        hesitations about them
      </li>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-unicyclePrimary text-8xl">
      Research
      <p class="text-slate-800">Analysis</p>
    </h1>

    <!-- <h2 class="">Research Insights</h2> -->

    <Image
      src={researchAnalysis}
      alt="research-analysis"
      class="pt-12 w-max rounded-md"
    />
    <article class="">
      <h2 class="pt-10">User Insights</h2>
      <li>
        Users expressed interest in a micro-mobility service that would remove
        high barriers to entry (making it easier to sign up and use more
        services more casually).
      </li>
      <li>
        Users have safety concerns, citing the lack of dedicated bike lanes,
        erratic driving, and worries about not having a helmet as significant
        deterrents to using micro-mobility services.
      </li>
      <li>
        Users are concerned about how much effort it takes to be situationally
        aware of both safety and where they are and need to go.
      </li>
      <li>Users like to ride for health and pleasure!</li>
      <li>Users opt for low-cost transportation options.</li>

      <h2 class="">User Empathy Map</h2>
      <p>
        A user empathy map was created to consolidate the results of the
        interviews and identify pain points.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div
      class="grid grid-cols-2 content-center grid-flow-row gap-4 [&>*]:rounded-md [&>div]:prose-sm [&>div]:p-7"
